'''Marko Jabbar Hussein Farji''' (born 16 March 2004) is a professional footballer who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]] for {{Italian football updater|Venezia}} club [[Venezia FC|Venezia]]. Born in Norway, he plays for the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq national team]].

==Early life==
Born in [[Grimstad]], Norway in 2004,<ref>{{cite web|title= – Jeg lærte mye i Grimstad om hvordan du behandler folk|accessdate=6 June 2024|url= https://www.gat.no/sport/i/y6ArKe/jeg-laerte-mye-i-grimstad-om-hvordan-du-behandler-folk|website=gat.no|date=13 December 2023 }}</ref><ref name="grim">{{cite web|title= Grimstad-gutt (19) ble matchvinner i eliteserien|url= https://www.agderposten.no/sport/i/l3xJW7/grimstad-gutt-19-ble-matchvinner-i-eliteserien |website=agderposten|date= 5 November 2023 |accessdate=6 June 2024}}</ref> he was born to Kurdish parents from [[Sulaymaniyah]], Iraq; he moved with his family to [[Gulskogen]] in the summer of 2020.<ref name="no"/> Aged eleven, Farji was on a try-out at [[Manchester City F.C. Under-21s and Academy|Manchester City's Academy]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Kristoffersen|first=Erlend Borren|date=26 April 2025|title=Toppscoreren fikk brutal beskjed fra Manchester City: – Ble lei meg|url=https://www.tv2.no/sport/fotball/eliteserien/toppscoreren-fikk-brutal-beskjed-fra-manchester-city-ble-lei-meg/17666483/|language=no|publisher=TV2|access-date=19 August 2025}}</ref>

==Club career==
In early 2019, after playing for the clubs academy for several years, Farji signed his first professional contract with [[FK Jerv|Jerv]], which lasted until the 2021 season.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fkjerv.no/nyheter/marko|accessdate=6 June 2024|title= MARKO ON A PROFESSIONAL CONTRACT!|website=fkjerv}}</ref>

He made his senior debut for [[Strømsgodset Toppfotball|Strømsgodset]] in 2022 in the quarter final of the Norwegian Cup against [[Sandnes Ulf]].<ref name="no">{{cite web|title=PROFESSIONAL CONTRACT FOR FARJI|accessdate=6 June 2024|url=https://www.godset.no/utvikling/nyheter/proffkontrakt-for-farji}}</ref> He signed a professional contract with the club aged 18 years-old in January 2023.<ref>{{cite web|date=14 January 2023 |title=Marko Farji (18) signed a professional contract with Strømsgodset|accessdate=6 June 2024|url= https://www.dt.no/marko-farji-18-skrev-proffkontrakt-med-stromsgodset-jeg-trives-kjempebra-i-klubben-og-byen/s/5-57-2054685|website=dt.no}}</ref> He scored his first league goal in the [[Eliteserien]] on 5 November 2023 in a 1–0 win against [[Tromsø IL|Tromsø]].<ref>{{cite web |url= https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/11/05/norway/eliteserien/tromso-idrettslag/stromsgodset-idrettsforening/3998928/|website=Soccerway|accessdate=6 June 2024|date=5 November 2023|title=Tromsø vs. Strømsgodset 0-1}}</ref><ref name="grim"/>

On 8 January 2026, Farji signed a four-and-a-half-year contract with [[Venezia FC|Venezia]] in Italy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Venezia FC|url=https://www.veneziafc.it/en/news/marko-farji-joins-venezia-fc|title=Marko Farji joins Venezia FC|date=8 January 2026|access-date=10 January 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
He has played for the [[Iraq national under-23 football team|Iraq U23]], featuring against United States U23 on 18 November 2023.<ref>{{cite web|title=USA U23 VS. IRAQ U23 1-1|website=Soccerway|accessdate=6 June 2024|date=18 November 2023|url= https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2023/11/18/world/under-23-friendlies/united-states-u23/iraq-under-23/4269325/}}</ref> As of May 2024, Farji had appeared for the U23 team seven times.<ref>{{cite news|last=Rougemont|first=Sigmund|date=28 May 2024|title=Marko på A-landslaget|url=https://www.godset.no/nyheter/marko-pa-a-landslaget|language=no|publisher=Strømsgodset Toppfotball|access-date=19 August 2025}}</ref>

In May 2024, Farji was called up to the [[Iraq national football team|Iraq]] team for their games in the [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification – AFC second round|Second Round]] of the Asian World Cup Qualifiers, but did not play in any of the games.<ref>{{cite news|last=Steien|first=Vegard Kjøllmoen|date=29 May 2024|title=Eliteseriekometen vraker Norge: – Jeg var veldig usikker|url=https://www.eurosport.no/fotball/eliteserien/2024/eliteseriekometen-vraker-norge-jeg-var-veldig-usikker_sto20007675/story.shtml|website=Eurosport|language=no|access-date=19 August 2025}}</ref> Later, in December, Farji was again called up, this time for games in the [[26th Arabian Gulf Cup|Arabian Gulf Cup]], where he got his debut against [[Yemen national football team|Yemen]], as a substitute in a 1–0 win.<ref>{{cite news|date=11 December 2024|title=Kåret til Årets unge spiller i Godset - tatt ut på det irakiske landslaget|url=https://www.drm24.no/stromsgodset/karet-til-arets-unge-spiller-i-godset-tatt-ut-pa-det-irakiske-landslaget/309681|language=no|publisher=Drammen Live24|access-date=19 August 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Iraq 1–0 Yemen|url=https://globalsportsarchive.com/match/soccer/2024-12-22/iraq-vs-yemen/3564370/|website=Globalsportsarchive|access-date=19 August 2025}}</ref> His first start for the national team, came in June 2025, against [[Jordan national football team|Jordan]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Match Report|url=https://www.the-afc.com/en/matches/asian-qualifiers/2026/2453108|website=The AFC|access-date=19 August 2025}}</ref>

